{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "LexRank represents sentences as nodes in a similarity graph, with edges weighted by TF-IDF cosine similarity [20].",
    "Low-similarity edges are pruned, and sentence salience is computed through eigenvector centrality.",
    "The top-ranked sentences are finally selected according to a target compression ratio.The second approach combined Latent Semantic Analysis (LSA) with HDBSCAN clustering to identify semantically coherent sentence groups.",
    "LSA reduces TF-IDF sentence vectors into a lower-dimensional latent space using singular value decomposition (SVD) [21].",
    "Sentences are subsequently grouped using HDBSCAN, a hierarchical density-based clustering algorithm [22]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
